<TITLE> Bela Nabi passes away </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Apr 10 (bdnews24.com) Bela Nabi, a leader of women's movement, passed away on Saturday at the age of 87. She was suffering from cancer for long. Bela Nabi died at 8:30pm in her daughter's house at Dhanmondi road 3, her family members told bdnews24.com. She is survived by her husband, two sons, one daughter and numerous well-wishers. Nabi was involved with communist movement. She acquired the position of vice president and international secretary of Jatiya Mahila Parishad (National Women's Council). During the formation of the council she worked closely with another veteran women's leader, Sufia Kamal. Bela Nabi was born in Patuakhali in 1923. bdnews
